    <h1> How to make chicken curry</h1>
    <br> <i>Chicken curry</i><p>is a dish originatiing from the 
        indiam subcontinent. it is common in the indiam subcontinent, southeast asia, and
        great britain, as well as int the caribbean.
    </p>
    <br>
    <h2>ingredients</h2><br>
    <strong>Following incredible are required to make chicken curry.</strong>
    <br>
    <ul>
    
        <li>1kg chicken, skineed and cut into pieces </li>
        <li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li>
        <li>1 inch cinnamon stick</li>
        <li>4 or 5 cloves</li>
        <li>4-5 green cardamom pods</li>
        <li>4 medium, red onion grated</li>
        <li>1 tsp fresh ginger paste, garlic paste  </li>
       <li>1/2 tsp ground coriander</li> 
        <li>1/2 table salt</li>
        <li>1 tsp garam masla</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chilli powder</li>
        <li>4 medium tomatoes, pureed</li>


    
    </ul>

    <h2>Instructions</h2><br>
    <ol>
        <li>trim the excess fat from the chicken and put these pieces in a large bownl</li>
        <li>place a medium nonstick saucepan over medium heat and add oil. when small bubbles appear at the bnotom of the pan, add the cardamom. cloves and cinnamon and salute for 1 min. when the spoce change colour and are fragrant, add the onions and salute for 3-4 min until golden brown. add garlic paste and salute. add the turmeric coriander cumin chillil powder stri well.</li>
        <li>add tomatoes and salute for 3-4 min</li>
        
        <li>transfer to a serving bowl, sprinkle with the gram masala and garnish with cilantro and serve.</li>


    </ol>
